<section class="lab-section alt">

<h2>Fun Mac & Cheese Chemistry Facts</h2>

<ul class="lab-facts">

<li>Adding pasta water to cheese sauce helps stabilize the emulsion because of its starch content.</li>

<li>Processed cheeses melt smoothly because they contain emulsifying salts.</li>

<li>Overheating cheese causes proteins to tighten, forcing fat to separate.</li>

<li>The ideal mac and cheese sauce temperature is between 150–170°F.</li>

<li>A blend of cheeses creates more complex flavors than a single cheese.</li>

</ul>

